Behind only New York, Tokyo and London, Paris stands as the world's fourth largest city. Today, one in six Frenchmen live in Paris or its suburbs. In every respect, Paris is the French center for politics, administration, commerce and the arts. It is also the favorite city for visitors to France Â­ almost three million per year. The most popular tourist attractions are the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre Museum (which holds the Mona Lisa) and Notre Dame Cathedral
